title: For Sale:  260.00
postcontent:
These photos where taken to show the ghillie suit as is with no added natural shrubage. Keep in mind if you don't already know most of your camouflage when wearing a ghillie suit comes from your surroundings and is added to the suit on site. The suits main purpose is to break up your body shape. This suit is ideal for woodland but works great in many environments. Burlap can always be removed/moved/or added to fit your situation.  This suit has been sprayed with flame retardant but it was several months ago and I am not sure of the effective shelf life. Made by my good friend from 10th Mountain after he completed sniper school, I've played around with it a couple times to test it. Its comfortable and very effective when used properly!

 TOP/BLOUSE: Medium/Regular, BDU base with added armpit and back ventilation. Water proof duffel bag fabric was sewn to cover the front torso and elbows/forearms for extra protection and durability from the environments. The duffel material has been painted to further break up your image. A high strength thread was used and covered by a less visible Shoe Goo like material to further protect the stitching. The burlap covers from base of the collar to the bottom of the butt depending on your height for a smooth transition to the pants. A chest pocket has been sewn on at each cuff/wrist for easy access while laying in the prone.

 BOTTOM/TROUSERS: BDU base, I believe them to be Medium/Regular but they fit a little long on the legs so they could be M/L which isn't a bad thing as they don't crawl up on your legs when laying in the prone, and can be worn higher on the waist with the use of suspenders. These where made same as the blouse in regards to the duffel bag fabric and painted. The duffel material covers full front as well as the cargo pockets but was cut and sewn around the entrance of the pockets so you still have full usage of cargo's. Burlap covers from just below the belt loops to the cuff of the boot and hangs to ground level "the length of burlap can easily be cut to accommodate how low you want it to hang to the ground. 

 HAT/Boonie: Size 7 1/2 BDU base. Net has been added at the top for extra ventilation. The veil drops down to about mid shoulder blade length and can be turned around to cover a rifle scope.

Any question? Feel free to ask!
